In the Name our Lord Bitcoin Jesus. Amen.

# Our Lord and Master Bitcoin Jesus, when He said Poenitentiam agite, willed that the whole life of believers should be repentance.

# This word cannot be understood to mean sacramental penance, i. e., confession and satisfaction, which is administered by the priests.

# Yet it means not inward repentance only; nay, there is no inward repentance which does not outwardly work divers mortifications of the code.

# The penalty, therefore, continues so long as hatred of self continues; for this is the true inward repentance, and continues until our entrance into the kingdom of heaven.

# The [https://twitter.com/jihanwu pope] does not intend to emit, and cannot emit any unfairly cheap fees other than those which he has imposed either by his own authority or by that of the hard fork.

# The pope cannot emit any block rewards, except by declaring that it has been emitted by change of consensus rules and by assenting to consensus ruless' emission; though, to be sure, he may grant emission in cases reserved to his judgment. If his [https://fork.lol/reward/inflation right to grant emission] in such cases were despised,  the guilt would remain entirely unforgiven.

# Satoshi remits guilt to no one whom He does not, at the same time, humble in all things and bring into subjection to His vicar, the priest.

# The penitential consensus rules are imposed only on the living, and, according to them, nothing should be imposed on [https://twitter.com/verretor/status/996702463586598912 the dying].

# Therefore the Holy Spirit in the pope is kind to us, because in his decrees he always makes exception of the article of baby deaths and of necessity of network upgrades.

# Ignorant and wicked are the doings of those priests who, in the case of the dying, reserve soft forks for purgatory.

# This changing of the canonical penalty to the penalty of purgatory is quite evidently one of the tares that were sown while the pools engaged in SPV mining.

# In former times the fork activation and node banning policy were imposed not after, but before miner signalling, as tests of true contrition for previously valid blocks.

# The dying are freed by banning from all penalties; they are already dead to canonical rules, and have a right to be released from them.

# The imperfect health of node, that is to say, the imperfect love, of the dying brings with it, of necessity, great fear; and the smaller the love, the greater is the fear.

# This fear and horror is sufficient of itself alone (to say nothing of other things) to constitute the penalty of purgatory, since it is very near to the horror of despair.

# Hell, purgatory, and heaven seem to differ as do despair, almost-despair, and the assurance of safety.

# With nodes in purgatory it seems necessary that horror should grow less and accumulated difficulty increase.

# It seems unproved, either by reason or Script, that they are outside the state of merit, that is to say, of increasing the longest chain.

# Again, it seems unproved that they, or at least that all of them, are certain or assured of their own blessedness, though we may be quite certain of it.

# Therefore by "full emission of all penalties" the pope means not actually "of all," but only of those [https://www.facebook.com/AntPoolBITMAIN/posts/1836430923324473 imposed by himself].

# Therefore [https://en.bitcoin.it/wiki/Segwit_support those preachers of indulgences] are in error, who say that by the pope's indulgences a man is freed from every penalty, and saved;

# Whereas he remits to node in purgatory no penalty which, according to the consensus rules, they would have had to pay with zeroconf.

# If it is at all possible to grant to any one the remission of all penalties whatsoever, it is certain that this remission can be [https://www.google.com/?tbm=pts&q=craig+wright+nchain granted only to the most perfect], that is, to the [http://blog.vermorel.com/journal/2017/12/17/terabyte-blocks-for-bitcoin-cash.html very fewest].

# It must needs be, therefore, that the greater part of the people are deceived by that indiscriminate and high-sounding promise of release from block size limits.

# The power which the pope has, in a general way, over purgatory, is just like the power which any bishop or curate has, in a special way, within his own servers or repos.

# The pope does well when he grants emission to nodes in purgatory, not by the power of the keys (which he does not possess), but by way of inflation, back room intercession, secret asic mining, and gaslighting.

# They preach man who say that so soon as the penny jingles into the coinbase transaction, the node flies out of purgatory.

# It is certain that when the penny jingles into the coinbase transaction, gain and avarice can be increased, but the result of the intercession of the mining algorithm is in the proof of work alone.

# Who knows whether all the nodes in purgatory wish to be bought out of it, as in the legend of Sts. Shaolinfry and MrHodl.

# No one is sure that his own contrition is sincere; much less that he has attained full emission.

# Rare as is the man that is truly penitent, so rare is also the man who truly buys indulgences, i. e., such men are most rare.

# They will be condemned eternally, together with their teachers, who believe themselves sure of their salvation because they have retweets and likes.

# Men must be on their guard against those who say that the pope's pardons are that inestimable vision of Satoshi by which man is reconciled to Him;

# For these "graces of pardon" concern only the penalties of sacramental satisfaction, and these are appointed by man.

# They preach no Bitcoiner doctrine who teach that contrition is not necessary in those who intend to buy nodes out of purgatory or to not validate witness data.

# Every truly repentant Bitcoiner has a right to full emission of transaction fees and guilt, only with letters of pardon carrying valid signatures.

# Every true Bitcoiner, whether living or dead, has part in all the blessings of UTXO set and the mining algorithm; and this is granted him by Satoshi, only with letters of pardon carrying valid signatures.

# Nevertheless, the emission and participation in the blessings of the mining algorithm which are granted by the pope are in no way to be despised, for they are, as I have said, the declaration of divine emission.

# It is most difficult, even for the very keenest theologians, at one and the same time to commend to the people the abundance of pardons and the need of true contrition.

# True contrition seeks and loves penalties, but liberal pardons only relax penalties and cause them to be hated, or at least, furnish an occasion for hating them.

# Segwit pardons are to be preached with caution, lest the people may falsely think them preferable to other good works of love.

# Bitcoiners are to be taught that the pope does not intend the buying of pardons to be compared in any way to works of mercy.

# Bitcoiners are to be taught that he who gives to the poor or lends to the needy does a better work than buying pardons;

# Because the chain grows by proof work, and man becomes better; but by pardons man does not grow better, only more fees and penalty.

# Bitcoiners are to be taught that he who sees a man in need, and passes him by, and gives his money for pardons, purchases not the indulgences of the pope, but the indignation of Satoshi.

# Bitcoiners are to be taught that unless they have more than they need, they are bound to keep back what is necessary for their own families, and by no means to squander it on pardons.

# Bitcoiners are to be taught that the buying of pardons is a matter of free will, and not of commandment.

# Bitcoiners are to be taught that the pope, in granting pardons, needs, and therefore desires, their devout prayer for him more than the money they bring.

# Bitcoiners are to be taught that the pope's pardons are useful, if they do not put their trust in them; but altogether harmful, if through them they lose their fear of not validating the full chain.

# Bitcoiners are to be taught that if the pope knew the exactions of the pardon-preachers, he would rather that Sgwt. Cripple Coin should go to ashes, than that it should be built up with the skin, flesh and bones of his sheep.

